{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κοιμ-άω</b>, <br /> <i>future</i> -ήσω, <i>Doric dialect</i> -άσω [ᾱ]: <i>aorist</i> ἐκοίμησα, <i>Epic dialect</i> κοίμησα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.372 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <i>future</i> -ήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 383.43 (Commagene, 1st c.BC), 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 4.64, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DDeor.” 4.4, etc.: _Epic dialect_ \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> κοιμήσατο, -αντο, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.241, 1.476 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> -ηθήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 574.6, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Asin.” 40, 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.37.3, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐκοιμήθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.411, +others, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 390, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 571e, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> κεκοίμημαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschrio Lyricus 8.2, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Gall.” 6 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>lull, put to sleep</b>, κοίμησον.. Ζηνὸς ὑπ᾽ ὀφρύσιν ὄσσε φαεινώ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.236; ἦ με.. κοιμήσατε νηλέϊ ὕπνῳ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.372; βλέφαρα μὴ κοιμῶν ὕπνῳ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 3 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>put to bed</b>, τὸν δ᾽ αὐτοῦ κοίμησε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.397 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of a hind, ἐν ξυλόχῳ.. νεβροὺς κοιμήσασα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.336. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>still, calm</b>, ἀνέμους, κύματα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.281, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.169; φλόγα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 597; κύματος μένος [prev. author] “Eu.” 832; εὔφημον.. κοίμησον στόμα [prev. author] “Ag.” 1247 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>soothe, assuage</b>, κοίμησον δ᾽ ὀδύνας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.524 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ᾧ (i.e. φύλλῳ) κοιμῶ τόδ᾽ ἕλκος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 650. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>middle</i> and <i>passive</i>, <b>fall asleep, go to bed</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 1.476, +others, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.9, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of animals, <b>lie down</b>, κατὰ ἤθεα κοιμηθῆναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.411: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ποῖόν τινα ὕπνον ἐκοιμ; 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Hiero” 6.7 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; βαθὺν κοιμηθῆναι (i.e. ὕπνον) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMar.” 2.3. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, ὅπως ἂν κοιμηθῇ [τὸ ἐπιθυμητικόν] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus [prev. cited] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> of the sleep of death, κοιμήσατο χάλκεον ὕπνον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.241; ἱερὸν ὕπνον κ. Callias Epigrammaticus “Ep.” 11.2 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>fall asleep, die</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 509 (Lyric poetry), 4th c.BC: Aeschrio Lyricus [same place]; ἐκοιμήθη μετὰ τῶν πατέρων LXX.3Ki.2.10, +others, compare “PFay.” 22.28 (1st c.AD), NT.Matt.27.52, NT.John.11.11, etc.; in epitaphs, “IG” 14.1683, etc.; κ. τὸν αἰώνιον ὕπνον [prev. work]929. \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> κοιμῶντο.. παρὰ μνηστῇς ἀλόχοισι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.246, compare 250 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: hence, of sexual intercourse, <b>lie with</b> another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.295, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 8(7).23; οὔ τινι κοιμηθεῖσα 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 213; παρά τινι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.68; σὺν δεσπόταισι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus [same place]; μετά τινος 4th c.BC: Timocles Comicus 22.2; ἀπὸ γυναικὸς ἀνὴρ τὰν νύκτα κοιμαθές “Berl.Sitzb.” 1927.157 (from Cyrene). \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> <b>keep watch at night</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 2, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.4, 9, “POxy.” 933.25 (2nd c.AD), etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.6</b></Level3> of things, <b>remain during the night</b>, οὐ μὴ κοιμηθήσεται ὁ μισθὸς παρά σοι ἕως πρωί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.19.13 \">LXX</a>]; ἡ κιβωτὸς ἐκοιμήθη ἐκεῖ[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.Josh.6.10. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.7</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>dream of</b>, μέταλλα χρύσεια [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Gall.” 6. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2837","accentedUnicode":"κοιμάω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2749","matchingForm":"κεῖμαι","stepTransliteration":"keimai","gloss":"to lay/be appointed","_zh_tw_Gloss":"放","_es_Gloss":"poner/ser designado","_zh_Gloss":"放"},{"strongNumber":"G2838","matchingForm":"κοίμησις","stepTransliteration":"koimēsis","gloss":"sleep","_zh_tw_Gloss":"睡覺","_es_Gloss":"sueño","_zh_Gloss":"睡觉"}],"shortDef":"(<i>pas